  "body": "For `shap.force_plot(matplotlib=True)`, if we specify `shap_values` that all have the same sign, the xlim looks wrong. This PR fixes that.\r\n\r\n## Minimal reproducible example\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport shap\r\nimport numpy as np\r\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\r\n\r\nnp.random.seed(0)\r\nbase = 100\r\ncontribution = np.r_[-np.random.rand(5)]\r\nnames = [f\"minus_{i}\" for i in range(5)]\r\n\r\nshap.force_plot(\r\n    base,\r\n    contribution,\r\n    names,\r\n    matplotlib=True,\r\n    show=False,\r\n)\r\nplt.show()\r\n\r\nnp.random.seed(0)\r\nbase = 100\r\ncontribution = np.r_[np.random.rand(5)]\r\nnames = [f\"plus_{i}\" for i in range(5)]\r\n\r\nshap.force_plot(\r\n    base,\r\n    contribution,\r\n    names,\r\n    matplotlib=True,\r\n    show=False,\r\n)\r\nplt.show()\r\n```\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8179588/213600136-42529445-e7f0-4fce-b775-ea4204eadb29.png)\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8179588/213600147-19474a1a-0369-4f6b-ba82-05704f7ec51a.png)\r\n\r\n## Results after correction\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8179588/213600629-39b29f2f-9045-432e-b279-045448e09e57.png)\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8179588/213600640-1d09e45c-0068-4985-82e1-f24e280c569f.png)\r\n\r\n",
